<h1 class="c28" id="h.xy1gz0hthuh3"><span class="c5 c18">Documentation: Publications Dashboard</span></h1>
<p class="c14"><span class="c11 c1 c19">Table of Contents</span></p>
<p class="c4"><span class="c12 c1"><a class="c9" href="#h.chrcoquq4bw7">About</a></span></p>
<p class="c4"><span class="c12 c1"><a class="c9" href="#h.u5bn3twko6o2">Dashboard Tabs</a></span></p>
<p class="c4"><span class="c1 c12"><a class="c9" href="#h.ccn8senky2ab">Data Sources</a></span></p>
<p class="c4"><span class="c12 c1"><a class="c9" href="#h.a799khcsf67w">Data Definitions</a></span></p>
<p class="c4"><span class="c12 c1"><a class="c9" href="#h.e2kxv7kc92qn">Data Download</a></span></p>
<h2 class="c10" id="h.chrcoquq4bw7"><span>About</span></h2>
<p class="c14"><span class="c5 c1">The Publications dashboard provides an overview of scholarly publishing at Stanford. It helps the university understand publication trends for different types of research outputs, fulfill reporting requirements, and plan services that support scholarly communication.</span></p>
<p class="c14 c16"><span class="c5 c1"></span></p>
<p class="c14"><span class="c1">Please submit feedback by emailing: </span><span class="c1 c7"><a class="c9" href="mailto:rialto-service@lists.stanford.edu">rialto-service@lists.stanford.edu</a></span><span class="c5 c1">.</span></p>
<h2 class="c10" id="h.u5bn3twko6o2"><span class="c5 c8">Dashboard Tabs</span></h2>
<p class="c14"><span class="c5 c1">The Publications dashboard features four dashboard tabs:</span></p>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_sf7hwoms6j7v-0 start">
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Stanford Overview</span><span class="c5 c1">: Counts of total Stanford publications, journals, and publishers from 2018 forward. Counts of total Stanford publications by publication type. List of the top journals by publication count. Publications can be filtered by publication type, federally funded, faculty authored, and year.</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Type Overview</span><span class="c5 c1">: Count of Stanford publications over time, by publication type. Publication types include: articles, books, chapters, preprints, datasets, and more. Publications can be filtered by federally funded, faculty authored, and year (2018 forward).</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">School Details</span><span class="c5 c1">: This page shows publication type information at the school level. A bar chart shows the publication types for each School, as a percent of publications within that School. A table shows the same information as count instead of a percent. Use the table filters to further refine publication type, publication year (2018 forward), federally funded, and more.</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Department Details</span><span class="c5 c1">: This page shows publication type information at the department level. A table shows the number of publications by type for each department. Use the table filters to further refine school, department, faculty authored, federally funded, and publication year (2018 forward).</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="c10" id="h.ccn8senky2ab"><span class="c5 c8">Data Sources</span></h2>
<p class="c14"><span class="c1">In order to create a highly precise dataset of publications by Stanford-affiliated researchers, we collect publications associated with an ORCID iD of a Stanford author, where that author has</span><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://library.stanford.edu/orcid-id&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444422285&amp;usg=AOvVaw2ymBQ-zC7rOsHUpcM6fovQ"> linked their ORCID iD with their SUNet ID</a></span><span class="c1">.  We supplement this dataset with publications approved by a Stanford researcher via their </span><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://profiles.stanford.edu/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444422604&amp;usg=AOvVaw2tzMp35lRP7nqF2oGd3x7q">Stanford Profile</a></span><span class="c5 c1">.</span></p>
<p class="c14 c16"><span class="c5 c1"></span></p>
<table class="c25"><tr class="c21"><td class="c27" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c17"><span class="c1">Want to be sure your publications are in our datasets?</span><span class="c1 c22"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://authorize.stanford.edu/orcid/OrcidInit?&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444423089&amp;usg=AOvVaw0zF-R87K_AgnOnQVfaIe7v"> </a></span><span class="c1 c13"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://authorize.stanford.edu/orcid/OrcidInit?&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444423220&amp;usg=AOvVaw3TO27IR4PGhumLqogQ9UAF">Link your ORCID iD to your SUNet ID</a></span><span class="c5 c1">.</span></p></td></tr></table>
<p class="c14 c16"><span class="c5 c1"></span></p>
<p class="c14"><span class="c5 c1">We query multiple publication sources by these ORCIDs and merge publication metadata by DOI or other unique metadata. Sources we query include:</span></p>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_qrivg451bxoy-0 start">
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://docs.openalex.org/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444423758&amp;usg=AOvVaw0S3meslDwKD_9nwPpYkF8Z">OpenAlex</a></span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.dimensions.ai/resources/api-documentation&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444423924&amp;usg=AOvVaw2WZwoqD3pcOXTa86JIS2wD">Dimensions</a></span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://developer.clarivate.com/apis/wos&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444424082&amp;usg=AOvVaw0AAGAdgg08L36fjMUx0gqr">Web of Science</a></span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK25501/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444424255&amp;usg=AOvVaw0wYrEJ9IZDONjd-HW23CLQ">PubMed</a></span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.crossref.org/documentation/retrieve-metadata/rest-api/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444424472&amp;usg=AOvVaw2TAPgX3DXUx1M89I8dcmCd">Crossref</a></span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c5 c1">Sul-Pub, the Libraries' bibliographic management system that feeds Profiles with publications from Web of Science and PubMed and also collects manually-entered publications from Stanford researchers. </span></li>
</ul>
<p class="c14 c16"><span class="c5 c1"></span></p>
<p class="c14"><span class="c5 c1">Where we have a DOI for a publication, we query for metadata from all sources, to create an aggregate record. We then enrich publications data with:</span></p>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_mkgoyim3k8az-0 start">
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1 c5">Federal funder data</span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c5 c1">Article Processing Charge (APC) data</span></li>
<li class="c0 li-bullet-0"><span class="c5 c1">Open Access category</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="c14 c16"><span class="c5 c1"></span></p>
<p class="c14"><span class="c1">We also harvest data from Stanford systems about authors' roles (e.g. faculty, staff, postdoc), school, and department, to allow filtering publications by these categories (see the </span><span class="c13 c1"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://rialto.stanford.edu/documentation/organization-data&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1781649444425824&amp;usg=AOvVaw35KyvAplpLpdLr5K6gGGw-">Organization Data</a></span><span class="c5 c1"> documentation for more information). We currently query metadata sources by ORCID for all authors, even if they are no longer affiliated with Stanford. This means we will have publications from before or after their affiliation with Stanford. Our dashboards restrict publications to 2018 forward.</span></p>
<p class="c14 c16"><span class="c5 c1"></span></p>
<p class="c14"><span class="c5 c1">We are always working to refine our data collection pipeline. Please let us know if you notice differences between the RIALTO data and your own records.</span></p>
<h2 class="c10" id="h.a799khcsf67w"><span class="c5 c8">Data Definitions</span></h2>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_yv8gz1w24wp6-0 start">
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">School</span><span class="c5 c1">: The primary Stanford school a researcher is affiliated with. In some cases, a researcher may have multiple affiliations. This dashboard only tracks their primary affiliation.</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Department</span><span class="c5 c1">: The primary Stanford department a researcher is affiliated with. In some cases, a researcher may have multiple affiliations. This dashboard only tracks their primary affiliation. </span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Publications</span><span class="c5 c1">: Publications are harvested from many different sources and merged on DOI. In the case of publications without a DOI, we make an effort to deduplicate these based on a combination of other identifiers and other metadata fields. This deduplication strategy is evolving but it is not perfect; some publications without DOIs will likely be duplicated.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_8j29av5mg7ut-0 start">
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Faculty Authored</span><span class="c5 c1">: True if at least one publication author is a member of the Stanford Faculty. Otherwise False.</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Publication Type</span><span class="c1">: </span><span class="c1 c3">Article</span><span class="c1">, </span><span class="c1 c3">Book</span><span class="c1">, </span><span class="c1 c3">Chapter</span><span class="c1">, </span><span class="c1 c3">Preprint</span><span class="c1">, </span><span class="c1 c3">Dataset</span><span class="c5 c1">, and more.</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Publication Year</span><span class="c5 c1">: Our data includes publications from 2018 to the current year. Note: Publication data for the current year is necessarily incomplete.</span>
</li>
<li class="c6 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c11 c1">Federally Funded</span><span class="c5 c1">: True if at least one of the publication’s funders is Federal. Otherwise False. Funder data for each publication is provided by Dimensions or OpenAlex, and a separate dataset identifies which funders are Federal.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="c10" id="h.e2kxv7kc92qn"><span class="c5 c8">Data Download</span></h2>
<p class="c20"><span class="c1">After filtering the data in a dashboard, you can download the resulting data by selecting </span><span class="c11 c1 c3">Choose a format to download</span><span class="c1"> in the dashboard toolbar menu  (next to </span><span class="c1 c3">Full screen</span><span class="c1"> and </span><span class="c1 c3">Share</span><span class="c5 c1"> buttons). Download format options include Image, Data, Crosstab, and more.</span></p>
<p class="c14"><span><img alt="" src="https://docs.google.com/docs-images-rt/APuouOdWZcfKkgQM-QmBc-i6BaSit52T1xZ3JydEiIFJh97XYLgP-WLamQHSSm4SJy1WHIpNhhTMetBIeFoPOUthDxwGicO9O2tEVwQ19elMczyBRQzE0_oDiObIHg2F95WAPXJ3q223RDfTnS7r3zsk=s2048" title=""></span></p>
<p class="c14"><span><img alt="" src="https://docs.google.com/docs-images-rt/APuouOdl6qp-7eQB_l6YZO6ibuWuS7UGJs29gIP8TAfn0r2E8jcUV99NlwxezKZTQcZB9JNcJzA-DvZ1m49Jjg77oa1JSy4O9ReAgEtjwf-l323RepnIF5mKBDmPQe_dWnIaDuNvZTeSvm1uFhAef_YQ=s2048" title=""></span></p>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_d8d9f7oyz7d-0 start">
<li class="c20 c23 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c1">Note: If the </span><span class="c11 c1 c3">Data</span><span class="c1"> option is not available, first click into the relevant chart or table on the dashboard page before selecting </span><span class="c1 c3 c11">Choose a format to download</span><span class="c5 c1">.</span>
</li>
<li class="c20 c23 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c1">The data will open in a popup window. Select </span><span class="c11 c1 c3">Download</span><span class="c5 c1">.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<p class="c14"><span><img alt="" src="https://docs.google.com/docs-images-rt/APuouOdeS4wKOEQ7uXQ24kCbt1vNrBYxxhjR7yIDoWFB_hsa9sp7WCvQkqCR3qovZtKv5JygUFt3cEaBoKJ6C9yTjJxpeg1WIHCc-cjnRLunHpiA-uul9CAibMBanqGZKV1ks2fGYRjZHe-eoIhNM6Vzx1w=s2048" title=""></span></p>
<ul class="c2 lst-kix_j9z4pvmmf2fh-0 start"><li class="c20 c23 li-bullet-0"><span class="c5 c1">Additional downloads can be found in the Downloads section of the RIALTO site, available to approved users upon request.</span></li></ul>
